cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) because it deals with cognitive radio networks and spectrum sharing between primary and secondary users. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) because it proposes a joint spectrum sensing mechanism that involves optimization and feedback. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) because it addresses the issue of safe spectrum access. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it involves modeling and solving a joint detection problem. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) because it deals with full duplex communication, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
